C<sub>12</sub>H<sub>22</sub>O<sub>11</sub> + O<sub>2</sub> + H<sub>2</sub>O
          <space/><link window="new" class="fullmarks" resource="http://www.fhsst.org/lOD">Click here for the solution</link></item>
          <item id="uid24">Barium chloride reacts with sulphuric acid to produce barium sulphate and hydrochloric acid.
<link window="new" class="fullmarks" resource="http://www.fhsst.org/lOW">Click here for the 	solution</link></item>
          <item id="uid25">Ethane (C<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mrow/><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:msub></m:math>H<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msub><m:mrow/><m:mn>6</m:mn></m:msub></m:math>) reacts with oxygen to form carbon dioxide and steam.
<link window="new" class="fullmarks" resource="http://www.fhsst.org/lOZ">Click here for the solution</link></item>
          <item id="uid26">Ammonium carbonate is often used as a smelling salt. Balance the following reaction for the decomposition of ammonium carbonate:
(NH<sub>4</sub>)<sub>2</sub>CO<sub>3</sub>(s)<m:math><m:mo>→</m:mo></m:math>NH<sub>3</sub>(aq) + CO<sub>2</sub>(g) + H<sub>2</sub>O(l)<space/><link window="new" class="fullmarks" resource="http://www.fhsst.org/lOB">Click here for the solution</link></item>
